author: Teemperor
body:
There are two JetUtil.h headers with the same header guards and
similar content in CMS. One is the header we remove here, the
otherw is HLTrigger/HLTanalyzers/interface/JetUtil.h. Having
two headers that define the same classes/functions but with
different properties/definitions is breaking the one definition
rule and will break C++ modules.

As this header doesn't seem to be used from what I can see, the
best option seems to be to just remove it.
title: Remove duplicate JetUtil.h
